<P1group id="p00003">
<Title><?start-line?>Immigration Act 1971: amendment</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>After section 3(9) of the Immigration Act 1971 insert the following new <?new-line?>subsections—</Text>
<BlockAmendment TargetClass="primary" Context="main" TargetSubClass="unknown" Format="double">
<P2>
<Pnumber>10</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>In making rules under subsection (2), the Secretary of State must have <?new-line?>regard to the following.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>11</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Rules must provide for persons seeking asylum, within the meaning of <?new-line?>the rules, to apply to the Secretary of State for permission to take up <?new-line?>employment and that permission must be granted if—</Text>
<P3>
<Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>a decision has not been taken on the applicant’s asylum <?new-line?>application within six months of the date on which it was <?new-line?>recorded, or</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<P3>
<Pnumber>b</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>an individual makes further submissions which raise asylum <?new-line?>grounds and a decision to refuse to treat such further <?new-line?>submissions as a fresh claim or on that fresh claim has not been <?new-line?>taken within six months of the date on which they were <?new-line?>recorded.</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>12</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Permission for a person seeking asylum to take up employment shall be <?new-line?>on terms no less favourable than those upon which permission is <?new-line?>granted to a person recognised as a refugee to take up employment.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00004">
<Title><?start-line?>Short title, commencement and extent</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act may be cited as the Immigration Act 1971 (Amendment) Act 2013.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act shall come into force on the day on which it is passed.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act extends to England and Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
